== Unicode ==
Kanbun were added to the Unicode Standard in June 1993 with version 1.1. Two Unicode &quot;kaeriten&quot; are grammatical symbols () for linking and reverse marks. The others are the organizational kanji for numerals (e.g. ), locatives (e.g. ), Heavenly Stems (e.g. ), and levels (e.g. ).

The Unicode block for kanbun is U+3190..319F:

